==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Merry-andrew
<hw>Mer"ry-an"drew</hw> <pr>(m⟦ecr⟧r"r⟦ycr⟧-⟦acr⟧n"dr⟦udd⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>One whose business is to make sport for others; a
buffoon; a zany; especially, one who attends a mountebank or quack
doctor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This term is said to have originated from one
<person>Andrew Borde</person>, an English physician of the 16th century,
who gained patients by facetious speeches to the multitude.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Merry-go-round</ent>⟦br⟧
